This article is a transcript of remarks given by various political figures, including Vice President Mike Pence and President Donald Trump, at a ceremony honoring Senator Bob Dole with the Congressional Gold Medal. The speakers praised Dole for his lifetime of service to the country and highlighted his character and selflessness. Pence specifically mentioned a moment in Dole's life when he voluntarily relinquished a position of authority in order to run for President. The article concludes with President Trump being introduced as the keynote speaker.